oai_dc:dc.dc:publisher: Heritage Protocol, Florida State University, Tallahassee, Florida.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Personal photographs of Grace Imogene Fox and Mary Jayne Martin-Vegue. Grace I. Fox earned her A.B. in Education from Florida State College for Women in 1928, eventually earning her Ph. D. in Education from Indiana University. Mary Jayne Martin-Vegue (formerly Mary Jayne Medlin) earned her B.S. in Education from Florida State College for Women in 1942, and earned her M.A. from Florida State University in 1949. Both would become faculty at Florida State University, as well as leaders in physical education in the state of Florida and nationally. These photographs are a part of the Grace I. Fox and Mary Jayne Martin-Vegue Collection (Accession No. HP-2008-025).
